		improve the diffusion of information within the group by
		leveraging fixed and mobile nodes that are exterior to the
		group. The fixed nodes are data sources, and the external
		mobile nodes are data relays, and we examine the trade off
		between the use of each in order to obtain high satisfaction
		within the target group, which consists of data sinks. We
		conducted an experiment in Cambridge, UK, to gather mobility
		traces that we used for the study of this content
