		constraints of a system that must function for months at a
		time without human intervention mean that demands on sensor
		network hardware are different from the demands on standard
		integrated circuits. This paper describes our experiences
		designing sensor nodes and low level software to control them.
		
		In the ZebraNet system we use GPS technology to record
